{
  "stem": "13096.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then, beside that, you know, whole day, the-- from the very first moment we arrive in the camp, it was a very, very bad smell into the air, that it was impregnated everywhere.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Whatever you touch, whatever you drink, it was like burning flesh.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That even now, you know, after 50 years, I got it still.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I can feel it in my nose-- that burning, like a very bad smell of this burning flesh, human flesh.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Anyhow, after this-- this thing, we were in quarantine for 40 days, because we were the arrived-- we arrive from-- from the trains.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we had all sort of, you know, germs on us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "For 40 days, nobody was-- you know, beside being, you know, selected for crematorium, they didn't gave us a bad-- I mean, a-- a very consistent job to do in the camp.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But they make-- they make us, you know, do things unbelievable, just to-- to-- to reduce us without any strength.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "For instance, one morning, they will say to you-- you see, there were piles of bricks there in the-- in the-- in the camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You must take three, four bricks-- they were very heavy-- in each-- in each hand.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And you must go by walk, and then the Germans will follow us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "By-- they were coming by jeeps, or whatever, to deposit those bricks so many miles away in the camp, which we were, you know-- we have to do it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then, when we were just carrying those bricks, the German would also tell us, you must sing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Because when we were transporting those bricks, we have to cross, you know, paths that come out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And the-- and the population, they will hear our voices.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
